Supervised Learning Model Evaluation
Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to evaluate a supervised machine learning model using multiple performance metrics. A Random Forest Classifier is trained on the Breast Cancer Wisconsin Dataset and evaluated using standard classification metrics.

Dataset

Dataset Name: Breast Cancer Wisconsin Dataset

Source: Scikit-Learn Built-in Dataset

Dataset Description

The dataset contains medical measurements of breast cancer tumors and corresponding diagnoses.

Total Samples: 569
Features: 30
Classes:
Malignant
Benign
Technologies Used
Python
Scikit-Learn
Model Used

Random Forest Classifier

Evaluation Metrics
Accuracy
Precision
Recall
F1 Score
ROC-AUC Score
Confusion Matrix
Expected Outcome

The project demonstrates how different evaluation metrics provide insights into model performance beyond accuracy alone.
